trend_summary: Over two decades the area remains lightly settled. Small clusters of houses gradually line the main east-west corridor, while scattered farm clearings increase, especially south of the reservoir. Northern forest cover thickens after earlier logging, and minor roads extend toward the lake, but no large urban cores emerge.
notable_changes: Incremental residential infill along the central east-west roadway.
Expansion of agricultural fields in the southern and southeastern sectors.
Regrowth of forest canopy in northern blocks previously cleared.
